  "NoContent": "No content",
  "Topic_17_RecordRequireNotification": "The customer was satisfied with the equipment STC800T5 / TC2080CE0736 as a whole. The technical delivery service was excellent. The staff was very attentive, answered all questions, and explained all the details of the machine in detail. The customer intends to continue purchasing.",
  "Topic_1_RecordRequireNotification": "The customer is currently bidding for the Northern Mining ESCONDIDA project and needs our company to cooperate with the preliminary preparations. The customer has returned to our company for negotiations and met with the senior management of the Crane Division to complete the signing of a preliminary strategic cooperation agreement for the project. The customer is currently satisfied with all the negotiation contents and our company will continue to support it until the bid is won next year.",
  "Topic_5_RecordRequireNotification": "RRC purchased a SAC600E, serial number Z006. The customer was extremely dissatisfied with the paint job and requested a complete repainting, with the cost to be borne by Sany (approximately £24,500). 1. Main problem: The level of refinement of the paint job needs to be improved urgently, the paint film in some areas is rough and transparent; the paint drips (relevant photos have been sent to the process) 2. Minor problem: The color number of the main engine paint job is deviated. (Relevant photos have been sent to the process)",
  "Topic_6_RecordRequireNotification": "The customer showed us the all-terrain vehicle model with special painting by Liebherr, and the customer hoped to get a similar model from Sany. Suggestion: To develop major customers, you need to do a lot of homework in marketing. Customers of crane rental companies are particularly interested in vehicle models. At present, the company's models are outdated and there is only one model of truck crane, which is in urgent need of upgrading. The introduction of customized painted equipment models is a weapon to conquer major customers and empower the front line.",
  "Topic_7_RecordRequireNotification": "1-The customer urgently needs a SIC130 device in June. The Sany factory has stock, but Sany's delivery time is too slow. The device is expected to arrive in Brazil in September.",
  "Topic_8_RecordRequireNotification": "1. The customer intends to purchase SCE8000A, but is concerned about the service/accessories situation. LB has a local service agent in Serbia that can provide one-hour troubleshooting. The customer hopes that Sany can also develop a local service agent. 2. Sany has no subsidiaries in Serbia, which will affect the customer's external financing purchases. The local bank requires that the financing agreement can only be signed after the equipment arrives in Serbia.",
  "Topic_9_RecordRequireNotification": "The customer reported that there was a problem with the manual for the SCE800TB-EV. The parts that Sany sent to the customer could not be found in the manual for the random parts. It was suspected that the manual was not updated to the latest version before delivery.",
  "Topic_10_RecordRequireNotification": "The customer once asked Sany Germany about the relevant parts, and the Sany Germany parts specialist replied: the parts are in stock, but the delivery cycle will take 2-3 weeks. The customer expressed dissatisfaction many times. It only takes 5 days for DHL express from Germany to Spain. He couldn't understand why Sany Germany would take 2-3 weeks to deliver the parts when they were in stock.",
  "Topic_12_RecordRequireNotification": "At present, the vibration frequency of our vibration handle of SAC600E/SAC2500E is set according to the opening size. It is related to the winch operation, but not directly related. In small openings, the handle vibrates, but the winch may not move. Customers suggest referring to Tadano and using the actual movement speed of the winch as feedback for the vibration frequency.",
  "Topic_13_RecordRequireNotification": "Our company has no load-bearing telescopic working condition for SAC600E/SAC2500E on the ground, which affects the purchasing intention of some customers who need to be constructed in the factory. This needs to be solved as soon as possible.",
  "Topic_14_RecordRequireNotification": "Customers of the E-series models suggested that the company develop an 8-axle, 450-ton, all-terrain equipment with superlift for Europe, but during the equipment product definition stage, it is necessary to fully communicate with market customers.",
